The article discusses the International Day of Persons with Disabilities and the importance of removing societal barriers for people with disabilities. The author highlights the commitment of the Administration to expand opportunities for Americans with disabilities, including through apprenticeship programs and increased engagement from business and community leaders. The article emphasizes the principles of human dignity, empowerment, and opportunity for all, and condemns the view that disabilities justify degrading or destroying human lives. The author calls for setting a global standard for treating people with disabilities with dignity and respect and working with other nations to advance their rights worldwide.